name: Version 0.17.2
body:
Ensures WP-CLI doesn't use cached WP minor upgrade partial archives in the major version upgrade process ([pull request](https://github.com/wp-cli/wp-cli/pull/1998)).

Since v0.17.0 ([pull request](https://github.com/wp-cli/wp-cli/pull/1320)), WP-CLI mistakenly cached partial archives in a lossy manner, which could result in a major version upgrade only upgrading the files from the cached partial archive.

Use `wp core verify-checksums` to make sure a given WordPress install has the correct copy of each file. If it doesn't verify, use `wp core download --version=$(wp core version) --force` to re-install WordPress.
